Detailed Description

An easy listitem provider to map static data to widgets defined in an XML file.

You can specify the data backing the list as an Vector of HashMap. Each entry in the Vector corresponds to one row in the list. The HashMap contain the data for each row. You also specify an XML file that defines the views used to display the row, and a mapping from keys in the HashMap to specific widgets.

const StringHashMapVector &  data,

const gaia::base::Array< gaia::base::String > &  from,
const gaia::base::Array< int32_t > &  to 
) [explicit]

The constructor of ISimpleListItemProvider.

Parameters:
contextThe context where the Widget associated with this ISimpleListItemProvider is running
dataA Vector of HashMap. Each entry in the Vector corresponds to one row in the list. The HashMap contain the data for each row, and should include all the entries specified in "from"
resourceResource identifier of a widget layout that defines the widgets for this list item. The layout file should include at least those named widgets defined in "to"
fromA list of column names that will be added to the HashMap associated with each item.
toThe widgets that should display column in the "from" parameter. The first N widgets in this list are given the values of the first N columns in the from parameter.
